        <mxCell id="S89zjXSp-3V75uFwfCcD-8" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;reasons for Foreign Direct Investments&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1. Desire to reap economics of large scale operations arising from technological growth&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;2. Desire to capture large and rapidly growing potential emerging markets with&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; substantially high and growing population&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3. Stable political environment and overall favourable climate in host country&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;4. The strategy to obtain control of strategic raw material or resource so as to ensure&amp;nbsp; their uninterrupted supply at the lowest possible price, usually a form of vertical integration&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;5. Desire to secure access to minerals or raw material deposits located elsewhere&amp;nbsp; and&amp;nbsp; earn profits through processing them in to finished goods (FDI in petroleum)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;6. Existence of relatively low wages due to labour abundance&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;7. Tax&amp;nbsp; differential and tax policies of the host country which support direct investments.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="-140" y="640" width="480" height="300" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
